  "prompt": "How do you invert your selection in Photoshop?",
  "response": "Inverting your selection in Adobe Photoshop is a straightforward process. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **Make Your Initial Selection**: First, use any of the selection tools (like the Marquee Tool, Lasso Tool, or Magic Wand Tool) to select the area you want to work with.\n\n2. **Invert the Selection**: Once your initial selection is made, go to the top menu and select **Select > Inverse** (or use the keyboard shortcut: **Shift + Ctrl + I** on Windows or **Shift + Command + I** on macOS).\n\n3. **Verify the Inversion**: After inverting, the previously unselected areas will now be selected, and the original selection will be deselected.\n\nThis technique is particularly useful when you want to select everything except a specific area, such as selecting the background instead of the foreground object.",
